# 15. Acceptance Criteria

### AC-1
Perform a complete review of the existing database schema and redesign where necessary without breaking existing functionality.

### AC-2
Remove only genuinely unused tables or columns after verifying they are not referenced anywhere in the application.

### AC-3
Introduce foreign keys and relationships only where they add real business value and do not overcomplicate the schema.

### AC-4
All business tables should include standard audit fields (`created_at`, `created_by`, `updated_at`, `updated_by`) where applicable.

### AC-5
Manual user-entered data (comments, approvals, notes, overrides) must always be preserved during refresh operations.

### AC-6
Refresh operations must perform intelligent merge/upsert logic instead of destructive delete-and-reinsert operations.

### AC-7
Record synchronization should use timestamps and business keys to determine the latest valid data.

### AC-8
Implement an automatic backup mechanism that exports the database to the local file system every 15 minutes.

### AC-9
On application startup, automatically restore the most recent backup if the H2 database is empty or recreated.

### AC-10
Implement a storage abstraction that supports both local file storage now and Azure Blob Storage in the future.

### AC-11
Document all Azure Blob Storage prerequisites and pending implementation tasks in `docs/pending-items.md`.

### AC-12
Generate production-ready DDL scripts for PostgreSQL and Azure SQL, including constraints, indexes, and audit fields.

### AC-13
Introduce database structures for Team Configuration while continuing to load runtime configuration from YAML during the current development phase.

### AC-14
Ensure the database design supports onboarding new teams using metadata only, without requiring code changes.

### AC-15
Move configurable iTrack metadata into the Team Configuration model while keeping YAML as the current runtime source.

### AC-16
Review and optimize indexes based on actual query patterns and expected production usage.

### AC-17
Maintain full backward compatibility with the existing UI, APIs, reports, background jobs, and business workflows.

### AC-18
Do not introduce unnecessary normalization, joins, or architectural complexity; prioritize maintainability and performance.

### AC-19
All future migration activities (YAML-to-DB, Azure Blob integration, Flyway/Liquibase adoption, production configuration) must be tracked in `docs/pending-items.md`.

### AC-20
The persistence layer should be production-ready, cloud-ready, and capable of scaling to additional teams and environments without requiring structural redesign.

